steps.title: Arrows Task
steps.text: This test measures how well you follow directions.

branchingNavigationRules.description: If last administration was within last 90 days than administer T.1L

criteria.name: lastAdministrationlessThanDays
criteria.description: If last administration was within last 90 days

branchingNavigationRules.description: If last administration was 90 or more days ago than administer I.1

criteria.name: lastAdministrationGreaterThanEqualToDays
criteria.description: If last administration was 90 or more days ago

steps.text: In this task you will see a row of arrows. You should choose the button that matches the way the MIDDLE arrow is pointing.
Sometimes all of the arrows point in the same direction
Always click the direction of the center arrow, even when they point in different directions.
Now let's try some more. Work as fast as you can without making mistakes.
Now we're going to take the Arrows test. Click "Repeat Instructions" if you want to repeat the instructions for this test. Otherwise click the "Begin Test" button to start the test.
Remember to click the button pointing the same direction as the center arrow. Work as fast as you can without making mistakes.
